  "body": "### Steps to reproduce:\r\n1. Create such amount of community chats or 1-1 chats to have the ability to scroll them.\r\n\r\n### Actual result:\r\n- When chats are scrolled on the community home page and hidden under the top navigation, the \"Discover\" section is shown on the current top navigation.\r\n- When chats are scrolled on the chats page and hidden under the top navigation, the \"Invite friends to Status\" section is shown on the current top navigation.\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/d292dd2c-9a3e-4261-a5e8-290226e9f066)\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/f81d4abb-696b-4918-8a17-4d69c489e5f8\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected result:\r\n- When chats are scrolled and hidden under the 'top nav', then 'discover' section should not be shown on the 'top nav'\r\n- When chats are scrolled on chats page and hidden under the 'top nav', then the 'invite friends to status' section should not be shown on the current 'top nav'\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/ee6a1664-7b6e-4c7b-a7e1-24325dcccd7e)\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/h9wo4GipgZURbqqr1vShFN/Communities-for-Mobile?type=design&node-id=4996-221009&mode=design&t=fMfIfJ3qH6JFZetO-0\r\n\r\n\r\n### ENV: \r\nNightly [5 Jul 2023]",
